	<presentation id="index">
		<title>Utility and Use of APIs: From Vision to Value</title>
		<toc class="abstract">APIs mean different things to different people. For some, they are simply technical tools for integrating software components. But for thought-leaders, APIs serve as strategic assets: They are digital building blocks that create what we call "option value", enabling large organizations like ours to be more flexible and resilient. Many companies aspire to become more modular and API-driven, yet translating this vision into strategy and ultimately action, is no simple task.</toc>
		<!-- Join Erik Wilde, renowned API strategist, OpenAPI ambassador, and industry thought leader, as he unpacks the critical success factors behind high-impact API programs. With a background spanning academia, enterprise consulting, and hands-on API innovation, Erik will share real-world insights on how developers drive broad participation, balance autonomy and structure with flexibility and realize the strategic potential of APIs. -->
